**who —** The Proton — A nucleon built of three quarks (up-up-down), one of the two residents of the nucleus. Positively charged, effectively stable (lifetime > 10³⁴ years).

**what —** A nucleon built of three quarks (up-up-down), one of the two residents of the nucleus. Positively charged, effectively stable (lifetime > 10³⁴ years).

**where —** ATM · The Atom  Framework inputs: the Standard Model & atomic/nuclear physics  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** ITS COUNT IS THE ELEMENT. The number of protons (the atomic number, Z) is the atom's identity — 1 proton is hydrogen, 6 is carbon, 79 is gold. Change the proton count and you change the element itself.

**how —** ITS COUNT IS THE ELEMENT. The number of protons (the atomic number, Z) is the atom's identity — 1 proton is hydrogen, 6 is carbon, 79 is gold. Change the proton count and you change the element itself.

